      "body" : "For those coming from Google, see here: <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/util/Comparator.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/util/Comparator.html</a> The documentation says, &quot;Compares its two arguments for order. Returns a negative integer, zero, or a positive integer as the first argument is less than, equal to, or greater than the second.&quot; Note that you can also use e.g. Integer.compare(int a, int b);"
